  "text": "The API server admission webhook chain is implemented under staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/. The architecture has three layers: (1) **Webhook admission controllers** \u2014 `mutating/plugin.go` and `validating/plugin.go` register the MutatingAdmissionWebhook and ValidatingAdmissionWebhook plugins, both embedding `generic/webhook.go`'s `Webhook` struct which provides the core `Dispatch()` entry point and `ShouldCallHook()` matching logic. (2) **Webhook call dispatch** \u2014 `mutating/dispatcher.go` and `validating/dispatcher.go` implement the `Dispatcher` interface (defined in `generic/interfaces.go`). The mutating dispatcher calls webhooks sequentially (with reinvocation support via `reinvocationcontext.go`), while the validating dispatcher fans out calls concurrently. Both use `util/webhook/client.go`'s `ClientManager.HookClient()` to get REST clients for the actual HTTP calls, and `request/admissionreview.go` to construct `AdmissionReview` request/response objects. (3) **Admission response aggregation** \u2014 `request/admissionreview.go`'s `VerifyAdmissionResponse()` validates and extracts response fields (allowed, patch, audit annotations, warnings). `errors/statuserror.go` converts denials into StatusErrors. `accessors.go` defines the `WebhookAccessor` interface providing a unified view of mutating/validating webhook configurations. `matchconditions/matcher.go` and `matchconditions/interface.go` implement CEL-based match conditions.",
